0,/Hotel_Review-g186338-d555057-Reviews-or0-Ibis_London_City_Shoreditch_Hotel-London_England.html#REVIEWS,Ibis London City - Shoreditch Hotel Reviews,Perfect location for tourists,"Stayed in a standard room with 1 double and 1 single/pull out bed. Room was compact but was fine for the 3 nights my children and I stayed. Room had everything needed, coffee, iron, hairdryer and a good size TV. Room (238) was street facing but no issue with noise at all. Bed was really comfy so we all had great nights sleep which was needed after long days exploring. Shower was decent and although bathroom would steam up within minutes after use would be normal again. The only issue was that there was no plug where the coffee making facilities were so I had to put the kettle on the floor in front of the mirror. Minor inconvenience and not sure whether that was an issue because furniture was moved to accommodate the additional bed?!   Location was excellent. Right next to the station which is on the District and Hammersmith line. So perfect for those wanting to explore London. Quite a few sites within walking distance also.  I was also able to check out late for ¬£10 which meant our mini holiday lasted longer without stressing about our luggage. Can't fault the staff either who were helpful and polite. All in all for the price, location, amenities etc it was perfect and I wouldn't hesitate to recommend or stay there again if the price was similar to what I paid.‚Ä¶",Date of stay: June 2021,5.0
